item.title: Lebanon Names New Prime Minister After Weeks of Political Uncertainty
item.description: Mustapha Adib, Lebanon’s ambassador to Germany, was named as the country’s next prime minister, an appointment that is unlikely to placate protesters who have sought a complete overhaul of the nation’s leadership.

item.title: Turkish Economy Weakens, Posing Challenge for Erdogan
item.description: A sharp economic contraction in Turkey threatens President Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s pledge to rapidly revive the nation’s economic prosperity.

item.title: Indian Economy Contracted at Record Rate Last Quarter
item.description: India’s economy shrank by a record 23.9% last quarter—the biggest blow the coronavirus pandemic has dealt to a major economy so far—as a nationwide lockdown and fear of the fast-spreading pandemic strangled spending.

item.title: In France, the Young Lose Their Jobs to Coronavirus
item.description: Young workers, having suffered from chronically high unemployment in France for more than a decade, are now bearing the brunt of the economic fallout from the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: India and China Trade Blame Over Troop Movements at Disputed Border
item.description: India and China accused each other of moving troops across their disputed border in recent days in violation of agreements between the two sides, the latest sign of tensions along the two countries’ disputed border.

item.title: Israeli Flight Lands in U.A.E. to Mark New Diplomatic Era
item.description: The first direct commercial flight from Tel Aviv arrived in the United Arab Emirates, carrying top Israeli and U.S. officials who marked a tangible step toward a new era of diplomatic ties between the two countries.
